Pakistan will fancy chasing this. Australia completely lost the plot in the middle overs, once the spinners came on. It was the combo of Afridi and Malik that did the damage, who kept the leash on Clarke and Haddin during their stand. Wickets kept falling at fairly frequent intervals, and even in the last ten, once the seamers came back on, Pakistan sustained very little damage. Join us in a bit for the run-chase.

Australia have had to labour for their runs here, and though the Pakistani spinners have done exceedingly well, the batsmen have had themselves to blame as well for failing to get going.

Getting singles has not appeared to be their main objective, but just surviving against spin. Saeed Ajmal has not used his variations to full effect today. The straighter one in his previous over was probably the only one, but both Clarke and Ferguson have even struggled to counter his regular offspin. They need to step up now, a score in the range of 200, it appears, won't be safe.
